Vice President Biden issued a statement regarding the testimony of GAO Acting Comptroller General Gene Dodaro at a Senate Committee hearing on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs. The statement emphasized the commitment to providing economic relief under the Recovery Act with accountability and transparency. The Vice President mentioned working with the GAO to oversee the spending of Recovery Act funds at the state level. He also discussed meeting with the Acting Comptroller General and the Senate Committee staff to discuss their joint commitment to scrutinizing Recovery Act spending. The Vice President expressed satisfaction with the establishment of oversight measures by states and stated his commitment to working with them to refine the reporting and oversight process.